snippet.textDisplay: 1:43 you can only hold up the mirror and put the palette on a table in front of you and dip your brush in the eyeshadows. I usually only take the original JH x Morphe eyeshadow palette while traveling because of its sturdy packaging and variety of eyeshadow options. I could create any natural/smoky neutral eye or a look with a pop of color with 1 palette. I have mirrors in my face palettes/compacts that are great to use on the go so a mirror isn't necessary for me, and also a large mirror in a palette like that would break easily and make it more expensive. I don't mind even if a cheap palette like this breaks, but I've lost too many expensive eyeshadows while traveling because they're usually so soft and fragile.
